"title": "8609: prayer, as praise and thanksgiving",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8609",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Prayer embraces praising God for who he is, thanking him for what he has already done, and looking forward with joy to what he has promised to do in the future.</p>\n<h2>Scripture exhorts God's people to praise and thank him</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:6\">PHP 4:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps66:1\">PSA 66:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:4\">PSA 68:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:1-Ps95:2\">PSA 95:1–95:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:1-Ps105:3\">PSA 105:1–105:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:19-Eph5:20\">EPH 5:19–5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:2\">COL 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:16-1Thess5:18\">1TH 5:16–5:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:15\">HEB 13:15</a></p>\n<h2>Praise and thanksgiving in prayer for God's goodness towards his people</h2>\n<h3>Praise and thanksgiving for deliverance and salvation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps65:1-Ps65:5\">PSA 65:1–65:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps66:5-Ps66:6\">PSA 66:5–66:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps81:1-Ps81:7\">PSA 81:1–81:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps124:1-Ps124:8\">PSA 124:1–124:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah2:1-Jonah2:9\">JON 2:1–2:9</a></p>\n<h3>Praise and thanksgiving for provision of material needs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:6\">MRK 8:6</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:36\">MAT 15:36</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps65:9-Ps65:13\">PSA 65:9–65:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:26-Matt26:27\">MAT 26:26–26:27</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:22-Mark14:23\">MRK 14:22–14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:19-Luke22:20\">LUK 22:19–22:20</a></p>\n<h3>Praise and thanksgiving for help in time of trouble</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:1-Ps34:4\">PSA 34:1–34:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps30:1-Ps30:12\">PSA 30:1–30:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:1-Ps40:5\">PSA 40:1–40:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:1-Ps103:5\">PSA 103:1–103:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps116:1-Ps116:19\">PSA 116:1–116:19</a></p>\n<h3>Praise and thanksgiving for the encouragement of other believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:3-Phil1:6\">PHP 1:3–1:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:8\">ROM 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:1\">2CO 8:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:16\">EPH 1:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:3\">2TH 1:3</a></p>\n<h2>Notable songs of praise and thanksgiving</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:1-Exod15:18\">EXO 15:1–15:18</a> <em>Moses, on crossing the Red Sea</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:2-2Sam22:51\">2SA 22:2–22:51</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:1-Ps18:50\">PSA 18:1–18:50</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:8-1Chr16:36\">1CH 16:8–16:36</a> <em>David, on bringing the ark to Jerusalem</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:46-Luke1:55\">LUK 1:46–1:55</a> <em>Mary, on learning that she was to be the mother of Jesus Christ</em></p>",
